<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-26T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-26T21:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/6–2748: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-27T11:00:00+09:00">June 27, 1948—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received June 27—1:43 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1163. Reference paragraph 5, Deptel 920 of June 24, Embtel 1149 of June
                            25 and Deptel 892 of June 17. Revised article IV (old numbering) of
                            bilateral aid agreement as agreed with Lapham mission was presented by
                                <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to Foreign Office June 25. Full
                            text contained in Embassy’s immediately following telegram.<note n="44" xml:id="d477fn44"><hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note> Foreign
                            Office brusquely rejected proposal by <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> June 26 as “undesirable <pb facs="0591" n="581" xml:id="pg_581"/> and unnecessary” and “creates impression that
                            administrative integrity of China is not strictly respected”.</p>
                        <p>Sent Department 1163, repeated Shanghai 534.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>